comment:
* Abstract class for receiving ADF provisioning state.
     * Should be extended by applications and set when calling
     * {@link UwbManager#provisionProfileAdfByScript(PersistableBundle, Executor,
     * AdfProvisionStateCallback)}

variables.name: REASON_INVALID_OID
variables.comment: * Indicates that the OID provided was not valid.

variables.name: REASON_SE_FAILURE
variables.comment: * Indicates that there was some SE (secure element) failure while provisioning.

variables.name: REASON_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: * No known reason for the failure.

methods.name: public abstract void onProfileAdfsProvisioned(@NonNull PersistableBundle params)
methods.comment:
* Invoked when {@link UwbManager#provisionProfileAdfByScript(PersistableBundle, Executor,
         * AdfProvisionStateCallback)} is successful.
         *
         * @param params protocol specific params that provide the caller with provisioning info
         *

methods.name: public abstract void onProfileAdfsProvisionFailed(@Reason int reason, @NonNull PersistableBundle params)
methods.comment:
* Invoked when {@link UwbManager#provisionProfileAdfByScript(PersistableBundle, Executor,
         * AdfProvisionStateCallback)} fails.
         *
         * @param reason Reason for failure
         * @param params protocol specific parameters to indicate failure reason

methodNames: public abstract void onProfileAdfsProvisioned(@NonNull PersistableBundle params)
public abstract void onProfileAdfsProvisionFailed(@Reason int reason, @NonNull PersistableBundle params)
